- A "company hierarchy" refers to the structure of an organization, where higher-level individuals supervise lower-level ones; 
- "Position in the company hierarchy" is determined by the level assigned in the `UserHierarchy` CTE, with lower levels indicating higher positions; 
- "Password reset trends" refer to historical data on how often users have reset their passwords, which can be used to assess security practices or identify potential issues.

sql:
SELECT DISTINCT u.email
FROM users u
JOIN user_activity_logs a ON u.user_id = a.user_id;
